import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.boxplot(x="location", y="precipitation", data=data)
    chart.axhline(data['precipitation'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['precipitation'].median()))
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation in Seattle and New York?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_max', data=data)
    chart.set(xlabel='Date', ylabel='Maximum Temperature (°C)')
    plt.title('How does the maximum temperature vary over time in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[data['location'] == 'New York']
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x='wind', y='temp_max', data=data)
    chart.set(title='What is the relationship between wind speed and temperature in New York?')
    chart.axvline(data['wind'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean wind speed: {:.2f}'.format(data['wind'].mean()))
    chart.axhline(data['temp_max'].mean(), color='green', label='Mean temperature: {:.2f}'.format(data['temp_max'].mean()))
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    data = data.groupby(['location', 'weather']).count().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='location', y='count', hue='weather', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition in Seattle and New York?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    seattle_data = data[data['location'] == 'Seattle']
    seattle_data = seattle_data[['temp_max', 'precipitation']]
    seattle_data = seattle_data.dropna()
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x='precipitation', y='temp_max', data=seattle_data)
    chart.axhline(seattle_data['temp_max'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean Temperature: {:.2f}'.format(seattle_data['temp_max'].mean()))
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)
